# eClerx × Talkpush hero visual — claude design prompt

Paste into claude design. Produces the right-side hero visual that replaces the current BEFORE/AFTER cards.

---

## Context

This is the hero of an account-specific deal room for eClerx, a BPO with 150–300 hires/month in Manila, large India operations, and a planned Cairo hub. Talkpush is pitching to consolidate eClerx's recruitment stack into one AI-driven flow.

The headline is already locked: "From weeks to a 24-hour hire — built for Manila, India and Cairo." The hero surface is dark. eClerx and Talkpush logos sit at equal prominence above the headline. Pink/lilac is the accent color. Don't redesign any of that.

The job is the visual on the right side of the hero. It needs to make the headline literal.

## Goal

One visual that shows, in three seconds and without body copy, how eClerx's current multi-week, multi-tool, multi-channel hiring process collapses into a 24-hour AI-automated flow on Talkpush.

## Concept: tangle to pipeline

A two-state diagram. Left side is the eClerx today: a tangled, scattered web of disconnected processes. Right side is Talkpush: a single clean horizontal pipeline. A motion or arrow connects the two.

### Left state — "Today · weeks"

Scattered nodes, lines crossing, muted neutrals. Each node is a piece of the current process:

- 8+ sourcing channels — Jobstreet, LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram, TikTok, referrals, internal ERP, website leads. Use small platform marks or labelled dots.
- Manual screening — recruiter glyph with a CV stack
- Versant assessment — proctored test desk glyph
- Manual scheduling — calendar with overlapping events
- Document chasing — email thread glyph
- Manual data entry — keyboard or form into Oracle

The tangle is the message. Lines should cross. Nodes shouldn't align to a grid. Slightly desaturated. A small caption under the cluster: "weeks · 6+ tools · manual handoffs."

### Right state — "24 hours · automated"

A single flowing pipeline, lit with the pink/lilac accent. Five clean steps in a horizontal line:

1. One inbox (all channels collapsed)
2. AI screening + TalkScore voice agent (replaces manual screening + Versant)
3. Auto-scheduling
4. Document AI (collect, OCR, validate)
5. Oracle sync

Each step is a small geometric icon with a one-word label below. The pipeline ends in a clear Oracle handoff. Caption under: "24 hours · one platform · AI-driven."

### Transition

Between the two states, an arrow or animated migration conveying collapse. If animated, the left nodes reorganize into the right pipeline. If static, a directional pink/lilac sweep with an arrow.

## Style

- Dark hero surface, near-black, matches the existing page
- Talkpush palette only. Pink/lilac accent reserved for the AFTER state, the 24-hour mark, and the active pipeline. Left state in muted neutrals.
- Type: small sans labels, all-caps state markers ("TODAY · WEEKS", "24 HOURS · AUTOMATED")
- Iconography: clean geometric line icons. No stock illustration. No human faces. No photography.
- Background can carry a subtle dot grid or radial glow under the AFTER pipeline. Nothing busy.

## Animation

This is the page's signature animation. One play on load, replayable on click.

- Duration: 3–5 seconds
- Sequence: left tangle visible → lines pulse → tangle reorganizes into the right pipeline → final state holds with a subtle pulse on the Oracle endpoint
- Reduced-motion fallback: static side-by-side composition with the arrow

## Aspect and placement

- Desktop: ~720–960px wide × ~480–560px tall, sitting to the right of the headline at hero widths up to 1440–1920px
- Mobile: stacks below the headline, full width, ~16:10 crop
- Bleeds against the dark hero surface; no card frame around the whole visual

## Constraints

- Do not change the headline, eyebrow, subhead, or logo lockup
- Stay inside Talkpush's palette
- If any product UI shows up inside the AFTER pipeline, it is candidate-side only (WhatsApp interview, voice TalkScore screen). No recruiter dashboards.
- The "8+ channels" framing and the Versant and Oracle names are load-bearing. Keep them visible.
- No competitor names other than Versant.

## Deliverables

1. Static hero composition — SVG and PNG, dark background
2. Animated version — Lottie or animated SVG, drops into the existing Vercel/Next.js template
3. Reduced-motion fallback — static PNG
4. Mobile crop — vertical stack version
5. Source file (Figma or equivalent) so labels and channel set can be edited later

## Success check

A reader who looks at the hero for three seconds, ignores the body copy, and never scrolls should walk away knowing:

- Today's process is many tools, scattered, slow
- Talkpush is one AI flow, fast, ending in Oracle
- It applies to Manila, India, and Cairo
